{
  "texts": [
    "As shown by the results, RAG should be an option to researchers when auditing a causal graph with any LLM.",
    "Multi-LLM Debate With ArbiterRAG doesn't eradicate the need for new, quality corpus and these are often elusive, especially in causal discovery, so we simulated quality data by mocking the true causal graph in the RAG experiment.",
    "To help overcome this in practice, we propose an alternate approach requiring no new corpus by employing multiple LLMs in a debate.",
    "The idea is that we can combine the wealth of knowledge from multiple LLMs to overcome the deficit of any individual LLM and/or lack of quality corpus.",
    "Specifically, we create the roles of two debaters, fulfilled by two LLMs, and the role of an arbiter, which is fulfilled by a third LLM."
  ]
}